    "explanation": "Store the next element in a variable on initialization or after each next() call.",
    "answer": "class PeekingIterator:\n    def __init__(self, iterator):\n        self.iter = iterator; self.next_val = self.iter.next() if self.iter.hasNext() else None\n    def peek(self): return self.next_val\n    def next(self):\n        res = self.next_val\n        self.next_val = self.iter.next() if self.iter.hasNext() else None\n        return res\n    def hasNext(): return self.next_val is not None",
